summary: An email from an Assistant United States Attorney in the Southern District of New York requesting a complete set of interview notes and FBI 302s from the entire case back to 2019 in preparation for a 3500 materials deadline. The email is addressed to unspecified recipients and copied to an unspecified individual.

events.title: 3500 Materials Deadline Preparation
events.description: An Assistant United States Attorney requests a complete set of interview notes and FBI 302s from the entire case back to 2019 in preparation for an upcoming 3500 materials deadline.

locations: United States Attorney's Office Southern District of New York
keyFacts: The email is dated September 9, 2021, and relates to the Ghislaine Maxwell case.
The prosecutor is requesting a complete set of interview notes and FBI 302s from the entire case back to 2019.
The request is made in preparation for a 3500 materials deadline, which refers to the Jencks Act requiring the government to disclose witness statements to the defense.
The email indicates ongoing legal proceedings in the Maxwell case as of late 2021.
The communication shows coordination between prosecutors and investigators in gathering evidence for trial.
